cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR 

The paper deals with image retrieval using deep learning techniques, specifically for firearm images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of fine-tuning and contrastive loss, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The use of neural networks for feature representation and classification also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with firearm images, which have implications for security and crime prevention, making it relevant to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
